I created my digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva, as it provides a variety of templates and easy-to-use design tools. My infographic is titled “Digital Literacy for Students” and highlights key concepts such as the meaning of digital literacy, useful digital tools, safe internet practices, professional online presence, and email etiquette. Each section is presented using short bullet points and icons to make the information visually appealing and easy to understand.

The design focuses on clarity and simplicity so that students can quickly grasp the importance of being digitally literate in today’s academic environment. I used different colors and icons to separate each section and make the infographic engaging.

One challenge I faced while creating the infographic was selecting the most important information and keeping the content concise without overcrowding the design. However, this helped me learn how to present information effectively in a limited space. Overall, this task improved my understanding of digital literacy and enhanced my design and communication skills.
